LAGOS – AXA Mansard Insurance Plc, a member of the AXA Group and global leader in insurance and asset management, has recorded Gross Written Premium of N28.64 billion, up 14 percent from N25.08 billion in March 2021. According to the company, the Net Premium Income of N11.57 billion, up 39 percent from N8.34 billion in March 2021, Investment and Other Income of N1.23billion, dip 25 percent from N1.64 billion in March 2021. Operating Expenses of N2.54 billion, up 1 percent N2.52 billion in March 2021while Profit before Tax of N470 million, declining 84 percent from N2.92 billion in March 2021 and Profit after Tax of N390 million, declining 85 percent from N2. 63billion in March 2021 Commenting on the results, Mrs. Ngozi Ola-Israel, the Chief Financial Officer, AXA Mansard Insurance, said: “We delivered double-digit revenue growth of 14% YoY from ₦25.07 billion to ₦28.64 billion and 39 percent YoY net income growth from 8.34 billion to 11.57 billion in the first quarter despite a challenging macroeconomic environment. However, we also grew Life and Health businesses by 58 percent and 24 percent respectively whilst our P & C business dipped five percent as a result of large unrenewable business written in 2021 and deliberate careful selection of risk in 2022.